%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eour%20own%20tasks%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20work%20together%20on%20single%20tasks%20until%20they%20were%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d1b34f9b-a5e8-438e-a7c1-9d336637ccc1%5C%22%3EI'm%20the%20planner%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20plan%20all%20our%20family's%20meals.%20I%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20meal%20rotation%20schedule%20after%20a%20long%20family%20meeting%20about%20dietary%20preferences%20and%20recipe%20likes%20and%20dislikes.%20Now%20I%20have%20a%20four-week%20meal%20plan%20that%20takes%20all%20the%20guesswork%20out%20of%20the%20age-old%20question%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20we%20having%20for%20dinner%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20decided%20we%20would%20aim%20to%20cook%20four%20to%20five%20times%20a%20week%2C%20sometimes%20eating%20the%20same%20meal%20two%20nights%20in%20a%20row%20to%20make%20things%20a%20little%20easier%20on%20us.%20On%20weekends%2C%20we%20will%20usually%20plan%20to%20make%20a%20meal%20on%20Friday%20night%20for%20dinner%2C%20then%20the%20leftovers%20for%20lunch%20on%20Saturday.%20These%20ideas%20aren't%20groundbreaking%2C%20but%20having%20them%20set%20as%20part%20of%20our%20overall%20plan%20for%20the%20week%20means%20we're%20more%20likely%20to%20stick%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20and%20her%20husband%20pose%20together.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c13c1ce98a37a4841f292b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20admits%20that%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20don't%20work%20well%20together%20in%20the%20kitchen%20due%20to%20their%20different%20styles%20of%20cooking.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rachel%20Garlinghouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f71efd9-37e3-46ef-8d9b-7f6784580134%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20husband%20does%20all%20the%20grocery%20shopping%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBelieve%20it%20or%20not%2C%20my%20husband%20enjoys%20the%20routine%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsave-up-to-80-percent-on-groceries-breaking-one-rule-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egrocery%20shopping%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Not%20me.%20I%20can't%20stand%20the%20hustle%20and%20bustle.%20The%20lights%20are%20too%20bright%2C%20and%20people%20seem%20to%20have%20no%20problem%20getting%20into%20my%20personal%20space.%20My%20husband%20pops%20in%20his%20earbuds%20and%20happily%20shops%20for%20our%20groceries%20once%20a%20week.%20Finding%20the%20right%20groceries%20is%20like%20a%20treasure%20hunt%20for%20him%2C%20he%20tells%20me%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20comes%20home%20with%20bags%20and%20bags%20of%20groceries%20for%20the%20six%20of%20us%2C%20and%20the%20kids%20help%20put%20everything%20away%20after%20thoroughly%20investigating%20the%20haul%20first.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22190c4aba-293f-43b0-bc00-2ef4a137e625%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20kids%20are%20our%20cooking%20assistants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20parent%20knows%20how%20hard%20it%20is%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long%20day%2C%20to%20make%20a%20meal%2C%20even%20when%20it's%20been%20carefully%20planned%2C%20and%20the%20groceries%20are%20in%20the%20fridge.%20To%20help%20with%20this%2C%20all%20of%20our%20kids%20have%20one%20or%20two%20%26quot%3Bfood%20helper%26quot%3B%20nights%20where%20they%20set%20the%20table%2C%20get%20out%20condiments%2C%20and%20help%20prep%20food%2C%20such%20as%20chopping%20veggies%20or%20firing%20up%20the%20oven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20it's%20stereotypical%2C%20but%20I%20hate%20when%20my%20husband%20is%20in%20the%20way%20in%20the%20kitchen.%20When%20he's%20cooking%2C%20I'm%20not%20in%20the%20space.%20When%20I'm%20cooking%2C%20I%20kick%20him%20out.%20Keeping%20this%20space%20allows%20us%20not%20to%20get%20in%20each%20other's%20way%20or%20on%20each%20other's%20nerves%20and%20allows%20us%20each%20a%20chance%20for%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%