ded%20Cancer%20Kids%20First%20after%20losing%20her%20grandfather%20and%20teacher%20to%20cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAt%20first%20her%20immigrant%20parents%20didn't%20understand%20her%20desire%20to%20lead%20a%20charity%2C%20she%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20she's%20a%20junior%20at%20Harvard%20teaching%20other%20young%20people%20how%20to%20become%20leaders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Foliviazhangofficial%2F%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOlivia%20Zhang%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguinrandomhouse.com%2Fbooks%2F808348%2Fyouth-by-olivia-zhang%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYOUth%3A%20The%20Young%20Person's%20Guide%20to%20Starting%20a%20Nonprofit%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%26quot%3B%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20was%20one%20of%20five%20children%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-gen-z-millennials-hopeless-economy-jobs-unemployment-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egrowing%20up%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20all%20resources%20were%20directed%20to%20just%20one%3A%20her%20brother.%20She%20was%20the%20first%20one%20in%20her%20family%20to%20graduate%20high%20school%2C%20then%20college.%20At%2030%2C%20she%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20with%20my%20dad%2C%20hoping%20that%20her%20future%20daughters%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20face%20the%20same%20barriers%20she%20did%20as%20a%20woman.%20I%20was%20born%20a%20year%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImmigrating%20was%20very%20hard%20for%20my%20parents.%20They%20often%20sent%20me%20to%20be%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-american-couple-expired-visa-left-america-reunited-guangzhou-china-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efamily%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20they%20could%20focus%20on%20their%20jobs%20and%20save%20money.%20My%20mom%20didn't%20know%20anything%20about%20American%20culture%2C%20so%20she%20copied%20and%20pasted%20her%20ideas%20from%20the%20people%20around%20us%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20other%20Chinese%20immigrants.%20She%20enrolled%20me%20in%20violin%2C%20piano%2C%20and%20Math%20Olympiad%3A%20all%20the%20extracurricular%20that%20other%20Asian%20American%20kids%20were%20doing.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20expected%20me%20to%20keep%20my%20head%20down%20and%20work%20hard%2C%20but%20I%20was%20always%20more%20interested%20in%20speaking%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d5201a5-7b8c-484b-9fc5-f14c498bea46%5C%22%3EAfter%20losing%202%20loved%20ones%2C%20I%20started%20a%20cancer%20nonprofit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspent-weekends-with-grandmother-she-made-me-understand-my-worth-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eclose%20with%20my%20grandfather%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20China%2C%20because%20we%20spent%20so%20much%20time%20together.%20At%20home%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20spent%20hours%20every%20school%20day%20with%20the%20same%20teacher%20in%20the%20afterschool%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%2013%2C%20both%20my%20grandfather%20and%20that%20teacher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-rare-terminal-cancer-living-funeral-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edied%20from%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20felt%20like%20my%20world%20was%20disappearing.%20I'd%20never%20lost%20anyone%20until%20then%2C%20and%20losing%20them%20so%20close%20together%20was%20devastating.%20I%20struggled%20with%20grief%20and%20depression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20grandfather's%20illness%2C%20I'd%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F8-ways-an-artist-can-make-money-2013-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eselling%20art%20to%20raise%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20treatment.%20After%20they%20died%2C%20I%20donated%20the%20remaining%20funds%20to%20St.%20Jude's%20Children's%20Research%20Hospital.%20Yet%2C%20I%20wished%20there%20was%20a%20way%20to%20see%20the%20tangible%20impact%20of%20my%20donation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20when%20I%20was%2014%20I%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cancerkidsfirst.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECancer%20Kids%20First%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20bringing%20joy%20to%20kids%20in%20hospitals%20through%20events%2C%20art%2C%20and%20treatment%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2230150641-3bc4-4849-b389-80296116a69b%5C%22%3EI%20grew%20the%20organization%20while%20in%20high%20school%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20poured%20everything%20into%20the%20nonprofit.%20My%20sophomore%20year%20was%20remote%2C%20so%20I%20had%20even%20more%20time%20to%20focus%20on%20Cancer%20Kids%20First.%20We%20had%20an%20influx%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-volunteer-your-time-during-the-coronavirus-pandemic-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evolunteers%20during%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20the%20organization%20really%20grew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20to%20block%20my%20time%3A%20after%20school%20on%20Mondays%2C%20Tuesdays%2C%20and%20Wednesdays%20I%20did%20homework.%20On%20Thursdays%20and%20Fridays%20I%20booked%20meetings%20with%20hospital%20leaders%20and%20volunteer%20coordinators.%20On%20walks%20to%20and%20from%20school%20I%20was%20answering%20emails%20and%20texts%20about%20the%20nonprofit.%20Looking%20back%2C%20I%20was%20micromanaging%2C%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20anyone%20else%20controlling%20the%20cause%20that%20was%20so%20close%20to%20my%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22women%20chatting%20non%20profit%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b835254d65ec51752a1299%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOlivia%20Zhang%20now%20has%20over%2040%2C000%20volunteers%20across%20the%20world.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Olivia%20Zhang%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20Cancer%20Kids%20First%20would%20be%20something%20big%20when%20we%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaking-tiktok-content-job-what-to-know-before-starting-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eposting%20on%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20first%20posts%20went%20viral%2C%20and%20we%20got%204%2C000%20volunteer%20applications%20in%20one%20night.%20Now%2C%20we%20have%20more%20than%2040%2C000%20youth%20volunteers%20in%2080%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee164038-5c71-4199-93f8-cc38905547c8%5C%22%3ENow%2C%20I'm%20teaching%20other%20young%20people%20how%20to%20lead%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20I%20tried%2C%20I%20didn't%20always%20succeed%20with%20balance.%20Sometimes%20I%20pulled%20all%20nighters%2C%20or%20ignored%20my%20homework.%20I%20was%20even%20failing%20pre-calculus%20at%20one%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20and%20neighbors%20didn't%20understand%20what%20I%20was%20doing%2C%20so%20I%20struggled%20to%20believe%20in%20myself.%20Even%20today%2C%20with%20all%20the%20success%20the%20nonprofit%20has%20had%2C%20my%20mom%20will%20still%20ask%20me%20what%20happened%20if%20I%20get%20an%20A-%20in%20a%20class.%20Yet%2C%20she's%20thrilled%20I'm%20at%20Harvard%20%E2%80%94%20we%20never%20thought%20an%20Ivy%20League%20education%20would%20be%20possible%20for%20our%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20young%20Asian%20woman%2C%20I%20wasn't%20encouraged%20into%20leadership.%20Because%20of%20that%2C%20I%20had%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20learn%20through%20trial%20and%20error.%20I%20want%20to%20change%20that%20for%20other%20young%20people.%20Cancer%20Kids%20First%20has%20so%20many%20young%20volunteers%2C%20that%20it's%20been%20natural%20to%20connect%20them%20with%20things%20like%20career%20training.%20I've%20seen%20that%20my%20generation%20has%20a%20real%20hope%20and%20desire%20to%20make%20an%20impact%20%E2%80%94%20we%20just%20need%20the%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-nonprofit-40000-volunteers-cancer-kids-first-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774444561000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b833364d65ec51752a1245%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-nonprofit-40000-volunteers-cancer-kids-first-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20launched%20Cancer%20Kids%20First%20as%20a%20teen%20after%20losing%20loved%20ones%20to%20cancer.%20A%20viral%20TikTok%20helped%20grow%20it%20to%2040%2C000%20youth%20volunteers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-nonprofit-40000-volunteers-cancer-kids-first-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Riz%20Ahmed%E2%80%99s%20Meta%20James%20Bond%20Casting%20Comedy%20%E2%80%98Bait%E2%80%99%20Is%20Too%20High-Concept%20for%20Its%20Own%20Good%3A%20TV%20Review%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774444500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236698438%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Amazon%20Prime%20Video%20comedy%20%E2%80%9CBait%E2%80%9D%20has%20two%20contradictory%20concepts%20that%20uncomfortably%20co-exist%20inside%20the%20same%20six-episode%20season.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20show%20is%20a%20deeply%20personal%20story%20from%20star%20and%20creator%20Riz%20Ahmed%20about%20what%20it%E2%80%99s%20like%20to%20be%20a%20South%20Asian%2C%20British%20and%20Muslim%20actor%20with%20deep%20roots%20in%20London%2C%20a%20biography%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Alisoncolleherman%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22JoJo%