imes%20I%20worry%20about%20my%20future.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Person%20looking%20at%20computer%20from%20behind%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2f35e58b5806618e7df7c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERohan%20Gore%20said%20he%20hasn't%20coded%20since%20December.%3Cp%3ENimito%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERohan%20Gore%2C%20an%20AI%20engineer%2C%20said%20he%20hasn't%20coded%20since%20December%2C%20and%20has%20mixed%20feelings%20about%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGore%2C%2038%2C%20said%20that%20he%20enjoys%20how%20he%20now%20has%20more%20time%20to%20focus%20on%20software%20architecture%20and%20design.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20he%20has%20concerns%20about%20what%20AI%20advancements%20mean%20for%20the%20future%20of%20his%20career.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Rohan%20Gore%2C%20a%2038-year-old%20AI%20engineer%20at%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3EReach3%20Insights%2C%20a%20market%20research%20firm%20based%20in%20Vancouver.%20His%20identity%20and%20employment%20have%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20graduated%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-study-software-engineering-changing-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecomputer%20science%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20in%202010%2C%20and%20I've%20worked%20in%20the%20industry%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20as%20a%20typical%20software%20engineer%20working%20on%20some%20of%20the%20interesting%20and%20complex%20problems%20in%20marketing%20research.%20Now%2C%20I'm%20an%20AI%20engineer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-creating-identity-crisis-for-software-engineers-coders-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emixed%20feelings%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20software%20engineering%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20completely%20handed%20off%20all%20my%20coding-related%20tasks%20to%20AI%20in%20December%2C%20and%20it%20did%20really%20well.%20I%20did%20not%20feel%20good%20about%20that%20initially.%20I've%20been%20coding%20for%20so%20long%2C%20and%20I%20realized%20at%20the%20time%20that%20coding%20is%20definitely%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20haven't%20coded%20since%20then.%20That's%20the%20new%20reality%20of%20my%20job.%20Just%20because%20AI%20has%20taken%20over%20my%20coding%20tasks%2C%20though%2C%20doesn't%20mean%20I%20can%20play%20outside%20all%20day.%20I'm%20still%20able%20%E2%80%94%20and%20expected%20%E2%80%94%20to%20produce%20the%20same%20level%20of%20output%20and%20quality%20of%20work.%20Sometimes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-fatigue-burnout-software-engineer-essay-siddhant-khare-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20feel%20burned%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20the%20expectation%20is%20that%20I%20should%20be%20doing%20more%20work%2C%20even%20though%20AI%20can%20take%20over%20some%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238040d0a-4df9-4776-9925-7729bf903565%5C%22%3EI'm%20excited%20about%20AI%20and%20enjoy%20how%20it's%20changed%20my%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-challenges-companies-fast-paced-innovation-strategy-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20needs%20a%20lot%20of%20guardrails%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20believe%20that%20my%20background%20and%20systems%20knowledge%20still%20make%20me%20pretty%20useful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20happy%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fentry-level-engineer-changes-career-development-ai-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20haven't%20coded%20in%20three%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20there's%20a%20lot%20that%20I'm%20doing%2C%20like%20software%20architecture%20and%20design%2C%20that%20isn't%20going%20anywhere.%20AI%20can%20help%20architect%20or%20design%2C%20but%20it%20needs%20a%20lot%20of%20hand-holding%20today.%20That%20makes%20the%20knowledge%20of%20software%20engineering%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20systems%20thinking%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20applied%2C%20which%20I%20love%20and%20am%20completely%20in%20harmony%20with%2C%20so%20it's%20a%20good%20state%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20coding%20for%20years%2C%20and%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20it's%20a%20means%20to%20an%20end.%20I%20never%20saw%20it%20as%20rocket%20science.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20nuance%20to%20coding%2C%20which%20can%20be%20frustrating%20and%20tiring%20to%20work%20with%20at%20times.%20So%2C%20I'm%20enjoying%20this%20next%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20also%20lets%20me%20do%20a%20lot%20more%20research%2C%20and%20faster.%20It%20allows%20me%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-changing-software-developer-role-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equestion%20product%20decisions%20and%20think%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20execute.%20As%20an%20engineer%2C%20I%20was%20constantly%20under%20delivery%20pressure%2C%20but%20now%20it%20frees%20me%20up%20and%20actually%20allows%20me%20to%20critique%20what%20a%20project%20manager%20is%20doing%2C%20because%20I%20understand%20the%20product%20decisions%20that%20are%20being%20made.%20It%20helps%20me%20take%20on%20a%20broader%20product%20engineering%20role%2C%20which%20I'm%20enjoying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20feeling%20happy%20that%20I%20can%20deliver%20at%20this%20pace%2C%20because%20that%20wasn't%20possible%20earlier.%20It's%20cool%20that%20I%20can%20make%20a%20feature%20in%20two%20or%20three%20days%20instead%20of%20a%20month.%20That's%20a%20crazy%20transformation%20that%20I%20feel%20happy%20and%20excited%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247117872-7421-4f21-866d-dea9006ab6ef%5C%22%3EI'm%20concerned%20about%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I'm%20enjoying%20the%20current%20state%2C%20there's%20always%20this%20behind-the-scenes%20thought%20of%2C%20%26quot%3BOk%2C%20what's%20next%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20technology%20is%20getting%20better%20every%20day.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI'm%20not%20comfortable%20with%20AI%20being%20in%20a%20state%20where%20it%20can%20run%20on%20its%20own%20forever.%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20I%20would%20do%20in%20that%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20feels%20weird%20that%20the%20job%20has%20changed%20so%20much.%20Sometimes%20I%20find%20myself%20speechless.%20I%20have%20so%20many%20thoughts%20and%20emotions%20going%20on.%20Most%20of%20them%20have%20turned%20into%20excitement%2C%20but%20the%20more%20I%20think%20about%20it%2C%20the%20more%20it%20turns%20into%20fear.%20Sometimes%20I%20felt%20intimidated%20because%20these%20agents%20are%20so%20powerful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20even%20openly%20said%20in%20my%20company's%20Slack%20that%20there's%20no%20way%20in%20my%20lifetime%20I%20could've%20coded%20something%20even%2010%25%20as%20good%20as%20these%20agents.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20a%20typical%20problem%2C%20most%20humans%20are%20no%20match%20for%20solving%20them%2C%20unless%20you're%20talking%20about%20the%201%25%20geniuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20feel%20defeated%20because%20coding%20was%20a%20skill%20I%20acquired%20over%20time%20and%20it%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20get%20to%20a%20state%20where%20I%20could%20do%20that%20well.%20It's%20not%20that%20I%20don't%20like%20the%20change%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20fear%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20happens%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-companies-replacing-human-employees-with-ai-layoffs-workforce-reductions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eall%20of%20this%20gets%20completely%20automated%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20people%20just%20ask%20AI%20for%20things%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-engineer-says-hasnt-touched-code-since-december-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774431241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2f36de98a37a4841f3352%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-engineer-says-hasnt-touched-code-since-december-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rohan%20Gore%2C%20an%20engineer%20at%20a%20market%20research%20firm%2C%20says%20he%20still%20feels%20useful%2C%20but%20has%20concerns%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20job.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-engineer-says-hasnt-touched-code-since-december-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Streaming%20Subscriptions%2C%20Pay-TV%2C%20Theatrical%20Box%20Office%20and%20Home%20Video%20Drive%20European%20Audiovisual%20Industry%20Revenue%20to%20%24165%20Billion%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774431176000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236698719%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Europe%E2%80%99s%20audiovisual%20sector%20generated%20some%20%E2%82%AC142%20billion%20(%24164.7%20billion)%20in%20revenues%20in%202024%2C%20driven%20largely%20by%20consumer%20spending%2C%20which%20accounted%20for%20more%20than%2050%25%20(%E2%82%AC72%20billion)%20via%20streaming%20subscriptions%2C%20pay-TV%2C%20cinema%20tickets%20and%20home%20video%2C%20making%20it%20the%20primary%20engine%20of%20growth.%20The%20European%20Audiovisual%20Observatory%20presented%20the%20latest%20data%20from%20the%20film%20and%20TV%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%