6048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22pokemon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2272d5b58f1f0f93367b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Keeble%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EScott%20Wool%20has%20been%20in%20the%20collectibles%20business%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThanks%20to%20his%20push%20into%20live%20selling%2C%20sales%20are%20growing%20like%20never%20before.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELive%20commerce%20allows%20sellers%20to%20answer%20questions%20and%20respond%20to%20customer%20feedback%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20Wool%2C%2060%2C%20has%20been%20in%20the%20collectibles%20business%20for%20decades%2C%20selling%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%2C%20toys%2C%20comics%2C%20and%20sports%20memorabilia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERunning%20a%20business%20has%20been%20a%20%26quot%3Broller%20coaster%20of%20a%20ride%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20nearly%20went%20bankrupt%20in%202013.%20About%2013%20years%20later%2C%20sales%20are%20growing%20like%20never%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20January%202025%20and%20January%202026%2C%20his%20eBay%20sales%20have%20spiked%20200%25%2C%20according%20to%20a%20screenshot%20of%20his%20seller%20dashboard.%20He%20credits%20that%20jump%20to%20two%20things%3A%20a%20boom%20in%20collectible%20card%20games%2C%20especially%20Pok%C3%A9mon%2C%20and%20his%20company's%20push%20into%20livestreaming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWool%20got%20into%20collectibles%20in%20his%20early%2020s%2C%20when%20he%20approached%20the%20owner%20of%20a%20local%20comic-book%20store%20and%20asked%20if%20he%20could%20buy%20into%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%20was%20%26quot%3Ban%20older%20gentleman%2C%20good%20friend%20of%20mine%2C%26quot%3B%20Wool%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20he%20said%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20I%20don't%20see%20why%20not.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20in%201987.%20Over%20time%2C%20the%20business%20evolved%20from%20physical%20stores%20into%20a%20much%20larger%20e-commerce%20operation.%20In%202026%2C%20Wool%20still%20has%20one%20retail%20store%20%E2%80%94%20Omni%20Comics%2C%20a%207%2C000-square-foot%20location%20in%20Wethersfield%2C%20Connecticut%20%E2%80%94%20but%20much%20of%20the%20company's%20energy%20is%20focused%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20introduction%20to%20e-commerce%20came%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20shortly%20after%20eBay%20launched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20saw%20this%20thing%20called%20eBay%2C%26quot%3B%20Wool%20said.%20He%20asked%20one%20of%20his%20employees%20to%20create%20an%20account%20and%20start%20listing%20items.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%2C%20'What's%20the%20worst%20that%20can%20happen%3F%20We%20have%20to%20move%20some%20excess%20inventory.%20Let's%20see%20if%20we%20can%20do%20some%20sales.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20launched%20on%20eBay%20with%20a%20clunky%20store%20name%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3Fh%3D76bc1c63ae763062defa07adec659c0b54a3939051ff02ee1549a5f68024ff95%26postID%3D69c177485ebd47b37dfd6091%26postSlug%3Dlive-selling-pokemon-cards-ebay-entrepreneurship-ecommerce-retail-2026-3%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.ebay.com%252Fstr%252Fpfootballpete4dhx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epfootballpete4dhx%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20asking%20an%20employee%20named%20Pete%20to%20set%20up%20an%20account.%20Pete%20happened%20to%20love%20football%2C%20and%20when%20%26quot%3Bfootballpete%26quot%3B%20was%20already%20taken%2C%20eBay%20auto-generated%20a%20different%20username.%20Wool%20didn't%20think%20much%20of%20it%20at%20the%20time%2C%20assuming%20he%20wouldn't%20sell%20much%20on%20the%20platform%20anyway.%20In%202026%2C%20the%20store%20still%20carries%20the%20name%2C%20has%20more%20than%20100%2C000%20followers%2C%20and%20has%20sold%20more%20than%202%20million%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20those%20early%20years%2C%20eBay%20was%20helpful%20but%20not%20yet%20a%20major%20driver%20of%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20get%20what%20you%20put%20into%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wool.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20listing%20products%20online%20was%20something%20his%20team%20did%20in%20their%20free%20time.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20gangbusters%2C%20but%20we%20did%20OK.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb8b2027-63b0-4770-b96f-eabb9abd339f%5C%22%3ELeaning%20into%20livestreaming%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWool%20said%20eBay%20invited%20his%20team%20to%20participate%20in%20an%20early%20livestreaming%20test%20in%202021%2C%20when%20the%20company%20was%20experimenting%20with%20the%20format%20with%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20sellers.%20He%20went%20in%20with%20modest%20expectations%20but%2C%20to%20his%20surprise%2C%20the%20first%20show%20took%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20%24225%2C000%20in%20maybe%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%2C%26quot%3B%20Wool%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20shocked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20part%20of%20that%20immediate%20success%20came%20down%20to%20having%20the%20right%20product%20%E2%80%94%20specific%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20right%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20market%20has%20changed%20over%20the%20years%2C%20explained%20Wool%2C%20who%20has%20been%20selling%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20since%20it%20was%20first%20introduced%20in%20the%20US%20roughly%2030%20years%20ago.%20Back%20then%2C%20demand%20was%20intense%2C%20but%20the%20customer%20base%20was%20mostly%20children%20and%20parents.%20Today%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20audience%20is%20broader%2C%20wealthier%2C%20and%20more%20global.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPok%C3%A9mon%20has%20become%20more%20than%20just%20a%20collectible%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20become%20a%20commodity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20some%20buyers%20now%20view%20collectible%20card%20games%20the%20way%20others%20view%20traditional%20investments%2C%20and%20that%20there%20are%20even%20investment%20funds%20dedicated%20to%20the%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELivestreaming%20has%20been%20just%20as%20important%20as%20the%20market%20tailwind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20pfootballpete%20being%20a%20listing%20on%20eBay%2C%20which%20is%20what%20we%20were%2C%20and%20competing%20100%25%20on%20price%2C%20now%20pfootballpete%20has%20personality%20behind%20it%20and%20trustworthiness%20because%20you%20see%20our%20people%20on%20camera%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20traditional%20e-commerce%20listings%20are%20static%2C%20livestreaming%20is%20interactive.%20Sellers%20can%20answer%20questions%20in%20real%20time%2C%20respond%20to%20customer%20feedback%20instantly%2C%20and%20build%20ongoing%20relationships%20with%20viewers.%20Wool%20said%20that%20matters%20in%20an%20online%20economy%20where%20trust%20is%20hard%20to%20establish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSocial%20media%20is%20wonderful%2C%20but%20most%20of%20it's%20static%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20I%20can%20run%20a%2030-second%20ad%2C%20but%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20really%20get%20to%20know%20who%20I%20am%20in%20a%20reel%20or%20in%20a%20social%20media%20post.%26quot%3B%20By%20contrast%2C%20livestreams%20can%20run%20for%20hours.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20can%20really%20get%20to%20know%20your%20personality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b346b9c-ddf1-4ebf-9ae8-a04048f18383%5C%22%3EWhat%20it%20takes%20to%20succeed%20as%20a%20streamer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPretty%20much%20anyone%20can%20start%20live%20selling%20on%20a%20platform%20like%20eBay%2C%20Whatnot%2C%20or%20TikTok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20do%20not%20have%20to%20have%20a%20retail%20store.%20You%20do%20not%20need%20a%20huge%20presence.%20You%20can%20have%20your%20own%20personality%20build%20the%20brand%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20You%20also%20don't%20need%20a%20lot%20of%20capital.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20really%20just%20start%20streaming%20with%20an%20iPhone%2C%20and%20that's%20all%20you%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20a%20low%20barrier%20to%20entry%20means%20more%20competition.%20As%20livestreaming%20has%20grown%20in%20popularity%2C%20Wool%20has%20spent%20more%20time%20thinking%20about%20ways%20to%20stand%20out.%20One%20of%20his%20ideas%20was%20to%20host%20a%20regular%20Friday%20night%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20stream%20held%20at%20the%20same%20time%20each%20week%20so%20viewers%20could%20build%20it%20into%20their%20routines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20like%20appointment%20television%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BBack%20in%20my%20day%2C%20we%20had%20to%20be%20home%20on%20Thursday%20night%20to%20watch%20Seinfeld.%20I%20thought%2C%20there%20is%20no%20stream%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20format%20helped%20create%20a%20recurring%20audience%20and%20sense%20of%20anticipation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWool%20has%20continued%20investing%20in%20the%20streaming%20arm%20of%20his%20business.%20He%20has%20about%2020%20streaming%20studios%20in%20Virginia%20and%20another%2020%20in%20Washington.%20Thanks%20to%20a%20large%20staff%2C%20he's%20essentially%20streaming%2024-7.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20streamers%20are%20those%20who%20build%20a%20community%2C%20understand%20their%20audience%2C%20and%20give%20viewers%20a%20reason%20to%20return.%20That%20means%20paying%20attention%20to%20what%20viewers%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20and%20what%20products%20they%20care%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETop%20streamers%20are%20also%20authentic%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20try%20to%20copy%20anybody%20else.%20That%20model's%20already%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20crowded%20market%2C%20he%20believes%20the%20real%20advantage%20comes%20from%20leaning%20into%20what%20makes%20a%20seller%20distinct.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20they're%20watching%20you.%20They%20could%20watch%2010%2C000%20streams%20of%20people%20opening%20packs%2C%20but%20they%20can%20only%20watch%20one%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3